<div class="container py-5">
    <h1 class="display-5 text-dark border-bottom pb-2 mb-4">🔐 Official Privacy Policy for SchoolManagement</h1>

    <p class="lead">
        This Privacy Policy describes how SchoolManagement ("the System," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and shares information in connection with your use of our web-based school administration application.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5 text-primary">1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect several types of information from and about users of our System:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>**Personal Identification Information:** Student names, teacher names, contact details (email, phone), and dates of birth.</li>
        <li>**Academic Data:** Enrollment status, class schedules, attendance records, and grades.</li>
        <li>**Technical Data:** IP addresses, browser type, operating system, and usage patterns within the application (for security and optimization).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-5 text-primary">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>The information we collect is used solely for the purposes of school administration, including:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>To manage student enrollment and class assignments.</li>
        <li>To track and report on academic progress and attendance.</li>
        <li>To communicate essential notices and information to students, teachers, and staff.</li>
        <li>To improve the functionality and security of the SchoolManagement application.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="mt-5 text-primary">3. Data Security</h2>
    <blockquote class="blockquote border-start border-primary border-5 ps-3">
        <p class="mb-0">We have implemented measures designed to secure your personal information from accidental loss and from unauthorized access, use, alteration, and disclosure. All data transmission is secured using industry-standard SSL encryption.</p>
        <footer class="blockquote-footer">SchoolManagement Security Team</footer>
    </blockquote>

    <div class="alert alert-info mt-4" role="alert">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 3, 2025. Please check this page periodically for updates to our policy.
    </div>
</div>